                        <li>The receipient will receive a link to a readonl=
y version of the current state of the map.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p><b>EXPORT -</b> To continue your work at a later dat=
e, simply export your map to a file:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Select 'Save / Import File' from the menu on th=
